462
00:44:43.755 --> 00:44:46.091
All right, here's the drill:

463
00:44:46.259 --> 00:44:49.679
The Germans are preparing a report
for the kaiser. It's a map...

464
00:44:49.847 --> 00:44:52.849
...that shows troop locations
and trench layouts.

465
00:44:53.017 --> 00:44:56.395
Their field commander's
sending the map via courier...

466
00:44:56.563 --> 00:44:58.482
...back to Germany
on a zeppelin today.

467
00:44:58.691 --> 00:45:00.108
How do we intercept it?

468
00:45:00.276 --> 00:45:03.779
You're gonna cross no man's land,
enter the enemy trenches...

469
00:45:03.947 --> 00:45:06.783
...and take the map from
the field commander's bunker...

470
00:45:06.951 --> 00:45:09.119
...before the courier
can reach the zeppelin.

471
00:45:09.287 --> 00:45:11.164
Sounds like fun.

472
00:45:11.332 --> 00:45:14.460
Oh, and I've arranged something special
for Amber.

473
00:45:14.628 --> 00:45:16.128
Give you some cover.

474
00:45:16.421 --> 00:45:18.215
Get you out of there when you're done.

475
00:45:20.676 --> 00:45:22.303
Let's go.

476
00:46:20.084 --> 00:46:21.793
What do you think?

477
00:46:23.714 --> 00:46:25.590
I like it.

478
00:46:42.612 --> 00:46:44.405
