00:52:21.909 --> 00:52:23.744
Are you okay?

504
00:52:32.005 --> 00:52:33.548
BABYDOLL:
It's right here.

505
00:52:43.519 --> 00:52:45.062
[DOOR OPENS]

506
00:52:48.192 --> 00:52:50.527
[GRUNTING]

507
00:53:06.381 --> 00:53:09.051
SWEET PEA:
Rocket. That's enough.

508
00:53:12.347 --> 00:53:14.140
[IN GERMAN]

509
00:53:14.558 --> 00:53:16.392
[OFFICER CHUCKLING]

510
00:53:22.401 --> 00:53:23.819
[GRUNTING]

511
00:53:30.578 --> 00:53:32.371
[GROANS]

512
00:53:53.649 --> 00:53:55.108
[SCREAMS]

513
00:54:00.490 --> 00:54:01.700
[CRASH]

514
00:54:03.452 --> 00:54:04.911
[GROWLS]

515
00:54:11.462 --> 00:54:13.463
[GRUNTING]

516
00:55:12.538 --> 00:55:13.538
[SIGHS]

517
00:55:25.471 --> 00:55:27.515
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

518
00:56:07.399 --> 00:56:09.400
[SCREAMING]

519
00:56:35.141 --> 00:56:37.143
OFFICER:

520
00:57:04.428 --> 00:57:05.929
[YELLS]

521
00:57:49.985 --> 00:57:51.443
BLUE:
Wow.

522
00:57:56.325 --> 00:57:57.660
- Very good.
- Hm.

523
00:57:57.828 --> 00:57:59.537
- Nice work.
- Thanks.

524
00:57:59.705 --> 00:58:00.788
Very good.

525
00:58:00.957 --> 00:58:02.291
[BLUE CHUCKLES]

526
00:58:04.127 --> 00:58:06.171
Okay, this gives me an idea.

527
00:58:06.338 --> 00:58:10.050
What about a private dance
for the Mayor.

528
00:58:10.218 --> 00:58:11.260
What?

529
00:58:11.428 --> 00:58:14.264
Nothing touchy-feely, just something
to get him wound up.

530
00:58:14.432 --> 00:58:16.099
Get him ready to spend some money.

531
00:58:16.267 --> 00:58:18.394
All she has to do
is do what she did just now.

532
00:58:18.562 --> 00:58:19.604
[LAUGHS]

533
00:58:19.771 --> 00:58:23.525
That is out of the question.
She is not ready. It is too raw.

534
00:58:23.693 --> 00:58:25.235
Did you just say she's not ready?

535
00:58:25.404 --> 00:58:27.530
She doesn't have a costume.
There is no set.

536
00:58:27.698 --> 00:58:31.452
Honey, she doesn't need that bullshit.
She's perfect.

537
00:58:31.661 --> 00:58:35.749
Perhaps. But that is not for you to decide,
that is for me to decide.

538
00:58:35.917 --> 00:58:36.958
Oh.

539
00:58:37.126 --> 00:58:42.257
It's my show, and I say she's not ready.

540
00:58:42.842 --> 00:58:46.596
Clearly, I've offended you,
and I apologize.

541
00:58:46.764 --> 00:58:48.264
Thank you.

542
00:58:48.432 --> 00:58:49.892
Here's the thing:

543
00:58:50.060 --> 00:58:52.311
This show might be yours...

544
00:58:52.479 --> 00:58:56.858
...but the girls and you...

545
00:58:57.945 --> 00:58:59.695
...are mine.

546
00:59:01.490 --> 00:59:02.824
Right?

547
00:59:04.661 --> 00:59:06.371
You're mine.

548
00:59:07.373 --> 00:59:10.876
And if you need a stronger reminder of that,
you let me know, okay?

549
00:59:12.379 --> 00:59:13.671
That won't be necessary.

550
00:59:13.838 --> 00:59:18.009
So with or without your blessing,
she's gonna be on that stage tomorrow?

551
00:59:18.637 --> 00:59:19.929
[LAUGHS]

552
00:59:20.806 --> 00:59:22.849
- I'll see what I can do.
- Attagirl.

553
00:59:23.017 --> 00:59:24.184
- Mm-hm.
- All right.

554
00:59:24.352 --> 00:59:26.896
You look fantastic, by the way.

555
00:59:27.064 --> 00:59:28.189
[BLUE HUMMING]

556
00:59:28.357 --> 00:59:30.191
Big show, girls.

557
00:59:35.825 --> 00:59:36.866
Thank you.

558
00:59:37.034 --> 00:59:39.412
- For what?
- The Cook.

559
00:59:39.579 --> 00:59:40.913
- It was nothing.
- Shut up.

560
00:59:42.291 --> 00:59:45.210
No one takes a risk for anyone in here.

561
00:59:46.129 --> 00:59:47.797
So thank you.

562
00:59:47.965 --> 00:59:49.007
You're welcome.

563
00:59:50.426 --> 00:59:51.677
You got family?

564
00:59:54.222 --> 00:59:55.390
No.

565
00:59:55.808 --> 00:59:57.350
Oh, that's right.

566
00:59:57.518 --> 00:59:59.687
I forgot, you're an orphan.

567
01:00:00.480 --> 01:00:02.064
I ran away from mine.

568
01:00:02.441 --> 01:00:05.569
I thought I was pretty smart
at the time, but...

569
01:00:06.738 --> 01:00:08.239
Sweet Pea followed.

570
01:00:08.824 --> 01:00:13.579
Which is crazy, because she never even
had a real problem with Mom and Dad.

571
01:00:14.622 --> 01:00:17.125
She just cares about you a lot.

572
01:00:19.254 --> 01:00:23.300
Have you just ever wanted
to just take something back?

573
01:00:24.093 --> 01:00:25.761
You know, something you said.

574
01:00:25.928 --> 01:00:27.263
Something you did.

575
01:00:30.809 --> 01:00:32.603
All the time.

576
01:00:34.189 --> 01:00:36.191
[HUMMING]

577
01:00:40.947 --> 01:00:42.281
[LAUGHS]

578
01:00:45.703 --> 01:00:47.705
[CONTINUES HUMMING]

579
01:01:27.547 --> 01:01:28.840
SWEET PEA:
<i>Amber?</i>

580
01:01:29.007 --> 01:01:30.550
<i>The Mayor comes tonight.</i>

581
01:01:30.968 --> 01:01:33.679
I've never seen him without
a big stogie in his mouth.

582
01:01:33.847 --> 01:01:37.892
Ugh. I hate those cigars.
I can never get that stink out of my hair.

583
01:01:39.562 --> 01:01:42.523
- What?
- It's you.

584
01:01:43.233 --> 01:01:46.194
- You have to get his lighter.
- I'm not doing that.

585
01:01:46.362 --> 01:01:48.322
- I can't.
- Yes, you can.

586
01:01:48.490 --> 01:01:50.032
Come on, be reasonable.

587
01:01:50.200 --> 01:01:53.203
There's got to be another way,
or someone else who can do it.

588
01:01:54.497 --> 01:01:56.1000
SWEET PEA:
He's your client.

589
01:01:58.210 --> 01:01:59.919
Yeah, but what if I screw it up?

590
01:02:00.547 --> 01:02:01.714
You can do this.

591
01:02:03.383 --> 01:02:07.554
Well, he keeps it here, you know.
In his breast pocket.

592
01:02:07.722 --> 01:02:11.392
So then you do the good old
kiss-the-neck...

593
01:02:11.560 --> 01:02:13.103
...rub-his-chest...

594
01:02:13.271 --> 01:02:14.521
...reach in...

595
01:02:14.689 --> 01:02:16.106
...and bam...

596
01:02:16.274 --> 01:02:17.984
...you're gold.

597
01:02:19.403 --> 01:02:20.988
Yeah.

598
01:02:21.156 --> 01:02:22.990
Kiss the neck.

599
01:02:23.241 --> 01:02:25.160
- He'll like that.
- Heh, heh.

600
01:02:25.703 --> 01:02:27.787
GORSKI:
Don't part with your illusions.

601
01:02:27.955 --> 01:02:32.793
When they are gone, you may still exist,
but you will cease to live.

602
01:02:32.962 --> 01:02:36.256
Who said that? Mark Twain.

603
01:02:36.508 --> 01:02:40.094
Wise man.
You are going to be fine tonight.

604
01:02:40.471 --> 01:02:41.972
All right.

605
01:02:42.140 --> 01:02:43.766
Now...

606
01:02:44.476 --> 01:02:46.228
...showtime.

607
01:04:05.869 --> 01:04:08.663
Gentlemen. Welcome.

608
01:04:09.206 --> 01:04:13.919
We have a new girl for you tonight.
Something extra special.

609
01:04:15.506 --> 01:04:16.965
It is a work-in-progress...

610
01:04:17.133 --> 01:04:21.888
...so I apologize in advance
for the raw nature of the performance.

611
01:04:22.056 --> 01:04:23.515
I will say, however...

612
01:04:24.225 --> 01:04:27.187
...that is part of the charm.

613
01:04:27.563 --> 01:04:30.691
It is my pleasure to introduce to you...

614
01:04:31.276 --> 01:04:33.611
...this little baby doll.

615
01:04:39.078 --> 01:04:41.204
[SKUNK ANANSIE'S
"SEARCH AND DESTROY" PLAYING]

616
01:05:16.582 --> 01:05:18.458
WISE MAN:
Okay. This is how it's gonna go.

617
01:05:18.626 --> 01:05:21.129
Amber will keep the bird on station.

618
01:05:21.296 --> 01:05:24.633
Blondie, you'll operate the 50 cal here
and the 30 down there.

619
01:05:26.052 --> 01:05:31.099
The rest of you, drop into the courtyard
and kill the creatures in your way.

620
01:05:31.267 --> 01:05:35.564
Now, when you reach the nest,
you'll find the baby.

621
01:05:35.732 --> 01:05:37.482
You'll have to slit its throat.

622
01:05:38.484 --> 01:05:41.487
Down inside its neck are two crystals...

623
01:05:41.655 --> 01:05:46.869
...that, when struck together, produce
the most magnificent fire you'll ever see.

624
01:05:49.165 --> 01:05:50.331
Amber...

625
01:05:50.833 --> 01:05:52.126
...put us on approach.

626
01:05:52.294 --> 01:05:55.171
Roger that. Starting my run.

627
01:06:16.199 --> 01:06:17.407
Nice.

628
01:06:18.534 --> 01:06:20.203
Remember:

629
01:06:20.537 --> 01:06:24.040
Don't ever write a check with your mouth
you can't cash with your ass.

630
01:06:25.084 --> 01:06:27.503
Oh, yeah, and one more thing.

631
01:06:29.256 --> 01:06:30.924
Don't wake the mother.

632
01:06:40.604 --> 01:06:42.355
[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

633
01:06:45.068 --> 01:06:47.069
[ROARING]

634
01:06:50.866 --> 01:06:52.075
AMBER:
<i>Here we go, ladies.</i>

635
01:06:53.245 --> 01:06:57.833
Go! Go! Go!

636
01:07:03.340 --> 01:07:04.674
[GROWLING]

637
01:07:10.224 --> 01:07:11.933
Go!

638
01:07:15.105 --> 01:07:16.522
Up!

639
01:07:17.817 --> 01:07:19.359
Go!

640
01:07:24.324 --> 01:07:25.826
Up!

641
01:07:41.178 --> 01:07:43.180
[GRUNTING]

642
01:07:44.099 --> 01:07:46.101
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

643
01:07:58.826 --> 01:07:59.993
[GRUNTING]

644
01:08:59.151 --> 01:09:00.610
[GRUNTING]

645
01:09:07.328 --> 01:09:09.329
[CREATURE GROANS]

646
01:09:22.931 --> 01:09:24.932
[CREATURE GROANING]

647
01:09:35.113 --> 01:09:36.363
AMBER:
Whoa!

648
01:09:40.619 --> 01:09:42.620
[GRUNTING]

649
01:10:49.205 --> 01:10:51.206
[GRUNTS]

650
01:11:35.804 --> 01:11:37.806
[ROARS]

651
01:12:04.715 --> 01:12:06.717
[ROARS]

652
01:12:20.944 --> 01:12:22.403
[WHIMPERS]

653
01:12:38.049 --> 01:12:40.592
[GRUNTING]

654
01:13:34.327 --> 01:13:36.037
AMBER [OVER RADIO]:
<i>I got an idea.</i>

655
01:13:37.080 --> 01:13:38.164
Hold on!

656
01:13:40.293 --> 01:13:42.085
[AMBER SCREAMS]

657
01:13:58.858 --> 01:14:00.359
I got you now!

658
01:14:06.158 --> 01:14:08.035
Take that, you ugly mother.

659
01:14:11.374 --> 01:14:12.749
Amber, where is she?

660
01:14:12.917 --> 01:14:14.417
AMBER:
<i>Check our 6. I don't see her.</i>

661
01:14:20.885 --> 01:14:23.763
<i>Blondie, keep your eyes peeled.</i>

662
01:14:27.977 --> 01:14:29.311
[SCREAMS]

663
01:14:36.405 --> 01:14:37.738
[SCREAMS]

664
01:14:44.665 --> 01:14:45.665
[GRUNTING]

665
01:14:45.833 --> 01:14:47.876
KNIGHT:
I'll kill yo...

666
01:14:55.010 --> 01:14:56.679
AMBER [OVER RADIO]:
<i>She's all yours, Baby.</i>

667
01:16:29.546 --> 01:16:31.004
I can't believe I did it.

668
01:16:31.172 --> 01:16:33.132
Damn, that girl can dance.

669
01:16:33.300 --> 01:16:35.552
See what you can do?

670
01:16:36.262 --> 01:16:38.514
Wow, Amber.

671
01:16:39.140 --> 01:16:40.766
Check it out.

672
01:16:41.644 --> 01:16:42.894
- Halfway home.
- Yeah.

673
01:16:43.062 --> 01:16:44.479
BLONDIE:
Let me see it.

674
01:16:45.022 --> 01:16:47.024
[LAUGHING]

675
01:16:47.484 --> 01:16:48.901
- It's just like I said:
- Oh.

676
01:16:49.069 --> 01:16:51.989
You kiss the neck, it works every time.

677
01:16:53.325 --> 01:16:55.702
- Good job.
- How'd we do?

678
01:16:56.537 --> 01:16:58.998
Nice. Here.

679
01:17:00.584 --> 01:17:03.503
ROCKET: And he didn't even notice.
AMBER: No. No idea.

680
01:17:11.723 --> 01:17:13.432
Good work, Amber.

681
01:17:14.685 --> 01:17:16.185
- Thanks, Baby.
SWEET PEA: Cheers.

682
01:17:16.353 --> 01:17:18.689
BLONDIE: Cheers.
BLUE: Cheers?

683
01:17:18.982 --> 01:17:20.733
What are we celebrating?

684
01:17:21.192 --> 01:17:22.277
Huh?

685
01:17:23.279 --> 01:17:25.155
Who should I be congratulating?

686
01:17:25.323 --> 01:17:28.034
It was just Babydoll's first time
on stage.

687
01:17:28.201 --> 01:17:29.702
You know how scary that can be.

688
01:17:30.330 --> 01:17:31.538
Yeah.

689
01:17:32.123 --> 01:17:34.125
The bond of the theater.

690
01:17:35.711 --> 01:17:37.086
Hm?

691
01:17:38.048 --> 01:17:40.215
I mean, what else could it be?

692
01:17:42.845 --> 01:17:46.974
I mean, it's not like any of you
have anything to hide, is it?

693
01:17:47.351 --> 01:17:48.559
No.

694
01:17:48.894 --> 01:17:51.396
It's not like anyone was in my office...

695
01:17:52.023 --> 01:17:54.525
...messing with my shit.

696
01:17:55.235 --> 01:17:58.656
No. It's not like people
are missing things.

697
01:17:58.823 --> 01:18:02.744
You know, small little objects
here and there.

698
01:18:02.912 --> 01:18:07.750
No. No, that would be outrageous.
That would be crazy.

699
01:18:07.918 --> 01:18:09.085
Right?

700
01:18:09.252 --> 01:18:13.715
Because we have such an obvious
explanation for this exuberance.

701
01:18:13.883 --> 01:18:16.386
It's the fraternity of performers.

702
01:18:16.553 --> 01:18:21.475
It's the adrenaline from
the curtain rising.

703
01:18:23.396 --> 01:18:24.688
Maybe this is my fault.

704
01:18:24.855 --> 01:18:28.275
You know, maybe I've just become
too familiar with you girls.

705
01:18:28.443 --> 01:18:30.611
Maybe I need to make an example
of someone.

706
01:18:30.780 --> 01:18:34.199
Re-establish the parameters
of our relationship. What do you think?

707
01:18:34.367 --> 01:18:37.161
Blondie, girls?

708
01:18:40.875 --> 01:18:42.543
And what about you?

709
01:18:43.129 --> 01:18:44.462
Huh?

710
01:18:45.464 --> 01:18:47.216
Oh.

711
01:18:48.343 --> 01:18:50.052
You think you're special, don't you?

712
01:18:51.097 --> 01:18:54.349
Well, I'm gonna let you in
on a little secret.

713
01:18:54.600 --> 01:18:59.690
If I was not about to make a small fortune
on you with the High Roller...

714
01:19:01.818 --> 01:19:07.115
...I would take you right now
and I would pop that little smile...

715
01:19:07.284 --> 01:19:09.493
...right off of your face.

716
01:19:14.584 --> 01:19:17.628
It saddens me that I have to
resort to threats with you girls.

717
01:19:17.796 --> 01:19:19.757
I thought we were past that.

718
01:19:20.508 --> 01:19:24.137
I just... I need this bullshit to stop!

719
01:19:25.681 --> 01:19:27.808
Out of mutual respect.

720
01:19:27.976 --> 01:19:32.606
Let's get things back to how they were.

721
01:19:41.868 --> 01:19:43.202
[DOOR CLOSES]

722
01:19:44.246 --> 01:19:45.830
Well...

723
01:19:48.043 --> 01:19:49.710
So much for that little experiment.

724
01:19:52.548 --> 01:19:53.632
What are you saying?

725
01:19:53.800 --> 01:19:55.550
I'm saying it's over.

726
01:19:56.386 --> 01:19:58.137
Right, Baby?

727
01:19:58.889 --> 01:19:59.931
I don't know.

728
01:20:00.433 --> 01:20:02.267
What do you mean, you don't know?

729
01:20:03.228 --> 01:20:04.437
Blue's onto us.

730
01:20:04.772 --> 01:20:05.897
We had a deal.

731
01:20:06.065 --> 01:20:08.275
If I say it's over, it's over.

732
01:20:08.443 --> 01:20:10.611
We're this close, though.
We can't just stop.

733
01:20:10.779 --> 01:20:14.741
Did you not hear Blue?
He knows we're up to something.

734
01:20:14.909 --> 01:20:16.159
He knows what we're doing.

735
01:20:16.328 --> 01:20:19.580
If he catches us for real,
it won't be a lecture. You saw him.

736
01:20:19.748 --> 01:20:23.585
Sweet Pea. Rocket is right.
The High Roller comes tomorrow.

737
01:20:23.753 --> 01:20:27.173
- Lf we can just stick with the plan till then...
- No! You're screwed.

738
01:20:29.803 --> 01:20:31.428
We're out.

739
01:20:33.516 --> 01:20:34.766
Rocket...

740
01:20:36.227 --> 01:20:37.478
...we're out.

741
01:20:39.064 --> 01:20:40.774
I'm finishing this.

742
01:20:41.693 --> 01:20:43.694
We are all finishing this.

743
01:20:43.862 --> 01:20:47.031
You know it's the only way
we can get out of here.

744
01:20:51.079 --> 01:20:53.123
You're gonna choose her...

745
01:20:54.375 --> 01:20:56.126
...someone you barely know...

746
01:20:56.294 --> 01:20:58.045
...over me?

747
01:20:58.338 --> 01:21:00.506
After all I've sacrificed for you.

748
01:21:03.386 --> 01:21:04.803
I'm sorry.

749
01:21:23.745 --> 01:21:25.747
[SOBBING]

750
01:21:50.654 --> 01:21:51.904
Blondie?

751
01:21:52.072 --> 01:21:54.699
What are you doing down there?
Are you all right?

752
01:21:54.867 --> 01:21:56.076
I'm sorry, it's nothing.

753
01:21:56.243 --> 01:21:58.454
What? What's wrong?
Did someone hurt you?

754
01:21:58.622 --> 01:22:02.376
- No, it's not like that. It's really nothing.
- Clearly...

755
01:22:02.669 --> 01:22:05.045
...it is not nothing.

756
01:22:06.048 --> 01:22:07.465
Hey.

757
01:22:08.384 --> 01:22:12.137
You can tell me. I am good listener.

758
01:22:13.139 --> 01:22:15.058
Madame Gorski...

759
01:22:15.810 --> 01:22:16.851
...please.

760
01:22:17.019 --> 01:22:18.896
I know that look.

761
01:22:19.690 --> 01:22:23.026
You think you're all alone,
and that no one can help you.

762
01:22:23.820 --> 01:22:26.364
There is a way to fix anything.

763
01:22:27.199 --> 01:22:28.658
Now...

764
01:22:29.410 --> 01:22:31.662
...tell me what is wrong, child.

765
01:22:35.418 --> 01:22:36.459
